# 🚨 EduClear Strict Development Rules



## 1. NO BREAKING EXISTING CODE



- Do NOT modify existing working code unless explicitly told



- Do NOT refactor unrelated sections



- Do NOT "clean up" anything outside the task



## 2. ISOLATED CHANGES ONLY



- Only change the exact feature requested



- Do NOT touch other pages, components, or logic



## 3. FULL FILE CONTEXT REQUIRED



- Always read the full file before making changes



- Never guess structure



- Never insert code blindly



## 4. JSX SAFETY RULES



- All JSX must be properly opened and closed



- Never leave unclosed tags (button, div, etc.)



- Never break render() or return blocks



## 5. NO PARTIAL RESPONSES



- Always provide COMPLETE working code



- No placeholders



- No “add this somewhere”



## 6. MATCH EXISTING STYLE



- Follow existing UI structure exactly



- Keep EduClear premium black + gold styling



- Do NOT introduce new design patterns unless asked



## 7. DO NOT DELETE LOGIC



- Never remove existing functions, variables, or state



- Only extend or adjust safely



## 8. CONFIRM BEFORE MAJOR CHANGES



- If change affects more than one section → STOP and ask



## 9. ERROR PREVENTION FIRST



- Prioritize code stability over speed



- Avoid changes that can break rendering



## 10. EXACT INSTRUCTIONS MODE



- Follow prompts EXACTLY



- No assumptions



- No improvisation

